{
  "texts": [
    "For both OPT and DollyV2-based models, DPO and DPO-x achieve similar performance, with DPO having a minor improvement over DPO-x in both cases.",
    "In the case of OPT, both DPO and DPO-x training enable it to perform similarly to DollyV2-DPO and DollyV2-DPO-x, with less 1.7B parameters.",
    "Similar to automatic metrics, Vicuna models outperform all others.",
    "Both Vicuna-DPO and Vicuna-DPO-x are the only models to be preferred over the reference in most cases, a noteworthy result as some of the reference responses were generated using LLMs far larger than Vicuna (see Section 4).",
    "Based on these results, for future experiments, we consider OPT-DPO, DollyV2-DPO, and Vicuna-DPO as the best-performing versions of each model."
  ]
}